infos.info: Hickerson writes that the show is on - Saturday or Thursday for 1/48 - Sunday or Saturday for 2/48-3/48 - Friday or Sunday depending upon location for 10/50-1/51 - Dunning show Theme Music as ' Night on Bald Mountain' - Some stories done were ' Plunder of the Sun' - As well as taking the role of narrator, William Conrad and Paul Frees were frequently cast with roles in the various stories. - ------------------------------------------------------------- - Opening: - NARRATOR: Tired of the everyday routine? Ever dream of romantic adventure in a far-off land? Want to get away from it all? We offer you...ESCAPE! - MUSIC: (Theme up full) - NARRATOR: Tired of the everyday grind? Ever dream of a life of romantic adventure? Want to get away from it all? We offer you . . . - MUSIC: (Dramatic chord) - NARRATOR: ESCAPE! - MUSIC: (Dramatic chords) - ANNOUNCER: ESCAPE! ...designed to free you from the four walls of today for a half-hour of high adventure. - MUSIC: (Theme up full) - Known as one of the last of many great high-suspense/horror/adventure half-hour programs. - ' Three Skeleton Key' - Source: Buxton and Owen, ' The Big Broadcast: 1920-1950'
